721041f-a.text:
Lexington Avenue, at the S. E. corner of East 63rd Street, showing at this location the Temple Rodelph Sholem (Followers of Peace). This structure was formerly the Beth-El Synagogue and erected in 1873. To the left is a view eastward to Third Avenue on the south side of 63rd St.
April, 1926
